description: From Latin intercalārius, from intercalāris, from intercalō, from inter (“among”) + calō (“call out, proclaim”).

entries.meaning: Describing a time period inserted between others; leap, (as in leap day, leap month, or leap year)

definitionGroups.group: (sciences, by extension) Inserted between other things

entries.meaning: (botany) of a meristem: situated between zones of permanent tissue, thus a shoot growing at the base of a leaf, in comparison with apical growth at the tip of a root or plant.
(entomology) of a wing vein: between the major veins common to insect wings.
